cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper focuses on identifying and tracking botnets using automatically generated domains (AGDs) through linguistic and IP-based features. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The use of machine learning and natural language processing techniques to analyze DNS traffic data also suggests the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social network analysis (cs.SI) being relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves data analysis and clustering techniques to group AGDs, which could fall under the category of data science (cs.DS).
